<pre><code><a href='https://github.com/ukparliament/egg-timer/blob/main/app/lib/calculations/forwards/commons_only_sitting_days.rb#L2' title='View on GitHub'>2</a>   module Forwards</code></pre>
<pre><code><a href='https://github.com/ukparliament/egg-timer/blob/main/app/lib/calculations/forwards/commons_only_sitting_days.rb#L3' title='View on GitHub'>3</a>     module CommonsOnlySittingDays</code></pre>


<p>The calculation counts a day whenever the House of Commons has an actual sitting day - and requires the start date and the number of days to count.</p>

<p>The calculation is set out in <a href="https://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2008/29/section/5#section-5-4A">section 5 (4A) of the Planning Act 2008</a>.</p>

<pre><code><a href='https://github.com/ukparliament/egg-timer/blob/main/app/lib/calculations/forwards/commons_only_sitting_days.rb#L9' title='View on GitHub'>9</a>       def commons_only_sitting_days_forwards( date, target_day_count )</code></pre>
<h2>We start counting on the <strong>first day when the House of Commons has an actual sitting</strong>.</h2>

<p>We continue to the <strong>day immediately following</strong> the start day.</p>

<p>If that day is or is followed by a House of Commons actual sitting day...</p>

<pre><code><a href='https://github.com/ukparliament/egg-timer/blob/main/app/lib/calculations/forwards/commons_only_sitting_days.rb#L15' title='View on GitHub'>15</a>         if date.next_day.first_commons_actual_sitting_day</code></pre>
<p>... we set the date to the day of the first House of Commons actual sitting day <strong>following</strong> the start date.</p>

<pre><code><a href='https://github.com/ukparliament/egg-timer/blob/main/app/lib/calculations/forwards/commons_only_sitting_days.rb#L18' title='View on GitHub'>18</a>           date = date.next_day.first_commons_actual_sitting_day</code></pre>
<p>... we have found the start of the scrutiny period.</p>

<pre><code><a href='https://github.com/ukparliament/egg-timer/blob/main/app/lib/calculations/forwards/commons_only_sitting_days.rb#L21' title='View on GitHub'>21</a>           @scrutiny_start_date = date</code></pre>
<p>... we&#39;ve found the first House of Commons actual sitting day so we start counting from day 1.</p>

<pre><code><a href='https://github.com/ukparliament/egg-timer/blob/main/app/lib/calculations/forwards/commons_only_sitting_days.rb#L24' title='View on GitHub'>24</a>           day_count = 1</code></pre>
<p>... whilst the number of days we’re counting is less than the target number of days to count ...</p>

<pre><code><a href='https://github.com/ukparliament/egg-timer/blob/main/app/lib/calculations/forwards/commons_only_sitting_days.rb#L27' title='View on GitHub'>27</a>           while ( day_count &lt; target_day_count ) do</code></pre>
<p>... continue to the <strong>next day</strong>.</p>

<pre><code><a href='https://github.com/ukparliament/egg-timer/blob/main/app/lib/calculations/forwards/commons_only_sitting_days.rb#L30' title='View on GitHub'>30</a>             date = date.next_day</code></pre>
<p>... and add 1 to the day count if this is a House of Commons actual sitting day.</p>

<pre><code><a href='https://github.com/ukparliament/egg-timer/blob/main/app/lib/calculations/forwards/commons_only_sitting_days.rb#L33' title='View on GitHub'>33</a>             day_count +=1 if date.is_commons_actual_sitting_day?</code></pre>
<p>... if the calendar has no record of what type of day this is, we can&#39;t calculate the end date, ...</p>

<pre><code><a href='https://github.com/ukparliament/egg-timer/blob/main/app/lib/calculations/forwards/commons_only_sitting_days.rb#L36' title='View on GitHub'>36</a>             if date.is_calendar_not_populated?</code></pre>
<p>... this error message is displayed to users ...</p>

<pre><code><a href='https://github.com/ukparliament/egg-timer/blob/main/app/lib/calculations/forwards/commons_only_sitting_days.rb#L39' title='View on GitHub'>39</a>               @error_message = &quot;It&#39;s not currently possible to calculate an anticipated end date, as the likely end date occurs during a period for which sitting days are yet to be announced.&quot;</code></pre>
<p>... and we stop looking through the calendar.</p>

<pre><code><a href='https://github.com/ukparliament/egg-timer/blob/main/app/lib/calculations/forwards/commons_only_sitting_days.rb#L42' title='View on GitHub'>42</a>               break</code></pre>
<pre><code><a href='https://github.com/ukparliament/egg-timer/blob/main/app/lib/calculations/forwards/commons_only_sitting_days.rb#L43' title='View on GitHub'>43</a>             end</code></pre>
<pre><code><a href='https://github.com/ukparliament/egg-timer/blob/main/app/lib/calculations/forwards/commons_only_sitting_days.rb#L44' title='View on GitHub'>44</a>           end</code></pre>
<p>If <strong>day immediately following</strong> the laying day is not a House of Commons actual sitting day <strong>and</strong> is not followed by a House of Commons actual sitting day...</p>

<pre><code><a href='https://github.com/ukparliament/egg-timer/blob/main/app/lib/calculations/forwards/commons_only_sitting_days.rb#L47' title='View on GitHub'>47</a>         else</code></pre>
<p>.. this error message is displayed to users.</p>

<pre><code><a href='https://github.com/ukparliament/egg-timer/blob/main/app/lib/calculations/forwards/commons_only_sitting_days.rb#L50' title='View on GitHub'>50</a>           @error_message = &quot;Unable to find a future House of Commons sitting day. It&#39;s not currently possible to calculate an anticipated end date, as the likely end date occurs during a period for which sitting days are yet to be announced.&quot;</code></pre>
<pre><code><a href='https://github.com/ukparliament/egg-timer/blob/main/app/lib/calculations/forwards/commons_only_sitting_days.rb#L51' title='View on GitHub'>51</a>         end</code></pre>
